<p>I have came across a question but I'm unable to optimize my code. Please tell me how can I optimize my code.</p>  <pre><code>    Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);     int max=0;     int a = in.nextInt();     for(int i=1;i&lt;a;i++){         for(int j=i+1;j&lt;=a;j++)         {             int d = i^j;             if(d&gt;max)                 max=d;         }     }     System.out.println(max); </code></pre>  <p>The explanation for the above code is:</p>  <ul> <li>The Xor of 1 and 2 is 3. </li> <li>The Xor of 1 and 3 is 2. </li> <li>The Xor of 2 and 3 is 1. </li> </ul>  <p>So, the maximum is 3.</p>